reviewText:
Doubtlessly, the best military aircraft simulation, no pros and cons here. If youre looking for the best experience with crafts like A-10, SU-25, MIGs, F-15, others, + variety of choppers - it's your choice. Specifically For F-18, F-16, F-14 look elsewhere, VRS things for Flight Simulator X, falcon BMS and others.
MUST HAVE, before even thinking of purchasing this one:
- TrackIR (absolute MUST);
- joystick and throttle (best if Thrustmaster H.O.T.A.S);
- rudder pedals (many would argue,  but thats a MUST, cuz you'll never get to use wheel brakes and yaw axis correctly  with else);
- capable PC (stronger the better cuz performance in this is a question of life and death sometimes);
- touchscreen monitor as wide and big as possible (optional, but VERY recommended, rids you of constant mouse  usage. anoying when right hand always on stick then mouse then back);
- voice recognition softwere and mic (useful for issuing radio comands and requests)
- persistence and patience;

Expences are high, and be ready for it. Be ready to spend hours, months and years learning and practising everything, and youll be very surprised of the result, it's like nothing else in PC gaming on my experience. Its not even a game, sometimes it's a hard brain work but that very rewarding when the mission is 100 % complete

